California International Marathon
Everything was fun and smiles with the perfect pacing and companionship.. I was already hearing the finish line cheering and inside Sac downtown when cramps appeared and walking was a challenge.. marathons are a beast.
Sometimes an injure will get you on the prep sometimes the race will make it but for those times that everything works to plan we keep trying and learning.
Time for a lot of fun bike riding, trail runs and some life re-adjustment.
Thank you for all the cheering and support on the course, everyone calling and messaging and all the friends who have shared part of the prep to this.. that honestly is the important and most meaningful part of this. The race is just a celebration.
Next one I hope it is on the trails and with the @satisfyrunning crew!
#cim #californiainternationalmarathon #runnningcultmember
